  "text": "Technology and science teacher orientations. To organize our identification of technology beliefs, like in our previous research , we adopted [CITATION_1] framework for technology-enhanced tools for student learning in science because we considered it to be compatible with a standards view of science literacy (AAAS, 1989; NRC, 1996 NRC, , 2011 . This is a three-dimension framework articulated as: tools supportive of mindful investigation of driving Science Teaching Orientations and Technology Tools 5 questions, tools serving as metacognitive scaffolds for building and revising scientific understanding, and tools supportive of collaborative construction of scientific knowledge. It should be noted that [CITATION_2] originally proposed this framework for inquiry learning tools, but we adapted these designations for identifying tools that play a significant role in science literacy. The dimensions are described in detail with our adaptations in Table 1 .",
